Police shot dead one man and wounded at least three others when they opened
fire on a mob attacking a white motorist in central Johannesburg, police
said.
Witnesses said a second man died when police opened fire to clear a blockade
erected by the protesting taxi drivers.
The killings came as two days of violence accompanied the strike by taxi
drivers alleging harassment.
