FT  03 FEB 93 / Israel, EC agree on investment
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LIONEL BARBER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ISRAEL and the European Community have agreed to lift obstacles to direct EC
investment in the occupied territories of the West Bank and Gaza, Mr Shimon
Peres, the Israeli foreign minister, said yesterday.
Mr Peres said the EC was becoming a world leader in foreign and humanitarian
aid and the accord would allow the EC to invest in housing, hospitals and
businesses in the West Bank without dealing with the Israeli authorities.
Israeli-EC relations improved this week after the Rabin government unveiled
an initiative aimed at bringing back about 100 of the Palestinian deportees
stranded in no-man's land in Lebanon and shortening the terms of the 300
others.
Mr Peres said the compromise cleared the way for talks to update a 1975
bilateral trade accord with the EC, but EC officials were more cautious,
describing it as a 'very good step' only.
Israel wants to free the movement of capital and services with the EC and
upgrade technological co-operation.
