TURKEY is to speed up its privatisation programme with an ambitious target
to raise revenues to TL25,000bn (Pounds 1.86bn) in 1993, more than five
times the sum realised in 1992, writes John Murray Brown in Istanbul.
Prime Minister Suleyman Demirel's ambitious sales target was unveiled
