<HEADLINE>
FT  03 FEB 93 / World News in Brief: Queen threatens to sue Sun over leak of
speech
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Lawyers acting for the Queen have threatened legal action against the Sun
newspaper for alleged breach of copyright after it printed the text of her
1992 Christmas Day speech two days early.
A letter from solicitors Farrer &amp; Co to editor Kelvin MacKenzie said court
proceedings would be started unless cash damages and costs were offered. The
Sun said it would vigorously defend the action.
</TEXT>
