<HEADLINE>
FT  03 FEB 93 / International Company News: Chrysler raises Dollars 1.78bn
in share issue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CHRYSLER, the US vehicle manufacturer, last night raised Dollars 1.78bn
gross when its international issue of 46m new shares was priced at Dollars
38 3/4 a share, - the closing price of the company's stock on the New York
Stock Exchange.
The issue is a considerable success for Chrysler, which has seen its share
price nearly quadruple since the start of last year as its financial
prospects have improved.
The company originally planned to issue 40m shares, but it has now sold an
additional 6m which it made available to the underwriters, led by First
Boston, to make up over-allocation of the stock to investors.
Chrysler's share price has performed robustly since the issue was announced
on January 11. It stood at Dollars 36 3/8 immediately before the
announcement, dipped a little afterwards, but then rose, helped by strong
fourth-quarter earnings.
The company has indicated it will use almost half the funds raised to reduce
the underfunding of its pension obligations. The shortfall stands at about
Dollars 4bn and Chrysler has left open the possibility that all the cash
could go to the pension fund.
