<HEADLINE>
FT  03 FEB 93 / International Company News: LTV moves deeper into red
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LTV, the steel group which has been operating under US bankruptcy court
protection since 1986, yesterday reported a fourth-quarter net loss of
Dollars 129m, compared with a net loss of Dollars 8.5m in the same period of
1991.
The increased loss was partly due to a Dollars 140m extraordinary charge for
LTV's estimated liability under a new law relating to retiree health
benefits in the coal industry. This was partly offset by a Dollars 60m
special credit. Sales totalled Dollars 947m, against Dollars 924m.
Fourth-quarter operating income was Dollars 13.4m, compared with a loss of
Dollars 70.3m in the same period of last year, with its steel business
losing Dollars 49.1m, against Dollars 54m a year ago.
For 1992 as a whole, LTV reported net income of Dollars 598.7m, compared
with Dollars 74.1m in 1991, thanks to a Dollars 737m gain on the sale of its
aerospace and defence business.
