</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ARIANE GENILLARD
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Frankfurt airport authorities yesterday announced a recruitment freeze
until April 1 in an effort to cut labour costs and stem losses.
Mr Wilhelm Bender, who took over as president of Flughafen Frankfurt Main
last month, warned that the company's net loss for 1992 would be 'as high as
the previous year'. The airport recorded a DM29.4m (Dollars 18m) loss for
the fiscal year ending December 31 1991.
Mr Bender blamed mainly increasing labour costs, which accounted for 43 per
cent of the company's overall expenses in 1992.
'We are faced with a drastic erosion of our basic capital if we don't change
direction,' he said. He did not expect the airport to return to profits in
the near future.
