and tax of ADollars 272m for the 53 weeks to June 27.
BHP has further consolidated the refinancing of its complex investment in
Beswick, the vehicle which controls around 20 per cent of BHP's own capital.
BHP directors yesterday announced that Westpac Banking Corporation had
agreed to hold its 'B' redeemable preference shares in Beswick until October
1996, subject to a put-and-call arrangement.
