FT  02 FEB 93 / Letter: Depressing not to have manufacturer among rights
issues
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr R M DANTZIC
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I find it somewhat depressing that the rights issue season should have
'kicked off' without any representation from the manufacturing sector. With
the government's heavy funding programme, equity capital is likely to be in
short supply and, accordingly, the City's traditional 'first come, first
served' method of allocating capital needs to be supplemented with a more
pro-active approach. Institutions, and company corporate advisers, should be
encouraging the manufacturers and exporters to re-finance to take advantage
of the opportunities created by sterling's decline rather than the retailers
and importers of whom we already have a surfeit.
R M Dantzic,
