<HEADLINE>
FT  02 FEB 93 / Parliament and Politics: Scientists warn of increase in
jobless
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CLIVE COOKSON, Science Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
URGENT government action is needed to regenerate UK industry, an all-party
alliance of politicians, industrialists and scientists warned yesterday.
The Parliamentary and Scientific Committee said: 'Without change, we shall
at best become a manufacturing arm of Japanese, American and German
companies whose governments have for years taken a more positive attitude to
science and technology and to manufacturing industry than UK governments.
At the worst, this will lead to chronic mass unemployment with ensuing
community unrest.' The committee does not usually advise the government
directly, but it has sent its report to the prime minister and ministers
responsible for industry, science and education. Its warning follows a
conference, which the committee organised with the Royal Society, on Japan's
emerging lead in technology.
Sir Gerard Vaughan, chairman, said: 'The message from the conference was
clear and extremely disturbing: unless we make major changes, this country
will become largely a labour market for other countries, without an adequate
manufacturing base of our own. This will be disastrous for our future
prosperity.'
</TEXT>
