FT  02 FEB 93 / TUC attacks proposal for Acas
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A PROPOSED change to the duties of Acas, the conciliation service, would
breach commitments imposed by international law, the Trades Union Congress
said yesterday.
The government's Trade Union Reform and Employment Rights Bill, now before
parliament, removes from Acas the duty to encourage collective bargaining.
The TUC argues that this would breach the International Labour
Organisation's Convention 98. This obliges signatories, which include
Britain, to encourage full development and use of arrangements for
collective negotiations.
