FT  02 FEB 93 / World Stock Markets: Argentina
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BUENOS AIRES ran into profit-taking following Friday's surge on government
measures to boost liquidity, cut banking costs and reduce interest rates.
The weighted Merval index of 19 most traded shares fell 18.20, or 4.25 per
cent, to 410.04, after Friday's 9.3 per cent gain and a fall of about 10 per
cent in the previous fortnight.
