There were 13,394 packages for the day, reports the Tea Brokers Association.
Landed demand was selective. Better liquoring Assams sold readily at
slightly easier rates, others declined by 5-10p. Bangladesh teas met limited
support below valuation. Bright Africans were a strong feature and often
dearer, but medium and plainer descriptions proved irregularly easier.
Offshore: only fair demand with prices 2-4p lower. The highest price
realised this week was 226p for a Rwanda PD. Quotations: quality 210, good
medium 175p, medium 152p, low medium 110p.
